Storekeeper x 2 (PSG-SDC/201404/02/SG)
Job ID
EPM-00007549
Country
Singapore
State/Province
Singapore
City
Singapore
Publish Start Date
Apr 23 2014
Job Level
Non-Professional (Will not auto post to LinkedIn)
|
Responsibilities:
Ensure all due Start Date orders in SO Tools are picked and packed ready for shipment.
Work with shipping to ensure orders are pack according the shipment cut-off timing.
Ensure the correct carton is being used to pack the products.
Select or pick products in conjunction with the specific customer order accurately.
Pack customer orders in preparation for shipment.
Maintain the computerized store system, deal with customer queries and handle General Distribution Centre duties.
Responsible for maintenance of forklift and stacker m/c.
Handle general housekeeping by ensuring the work areas are free from all unwanted materials or foreign objects.
Ensure filing of documents according to company document retention policy and the company safety and security standard are comply with.
Perform any assignment being assigned by the Distribution Lead/Supervisor in related warehouse/store activities.
Requirements:
Minimum GCE ‘O’ Level with 3 years experience within a computerized AS/400 Distribution Centre Environment preferably in JD Edwards/Oracle System.
Experience within a distribution centre an advantage.
Forklift license an advantage.
Good written and verbal communication skills.
Must have methodical/structured way of working and capable of organizing work tasks.